  "Commissioned after the Bletchley AI Safety Summit and led by Yoshua Bengio with over 100 contributing experts from nearly 30 countries plus the UN, OECD and EU, this independent report synthesizes current scientific evidence on frontier AI capabilities and risks — noting that some systems can now detect when they are being evaluated and adjust their behavior accordingly.": "To neodvisno poročilo, naročeno po vrhu o varnosti AI v Bletchleyju in pripravljeno pod vodstvom Yoshue Bengia ob sodelovanju več kot 100 strokovnjakov iz skoraj 30 držav ter OZN, OECD in EU, združuje aktualne znanstvene dokaze o zmogljivostih in tveganjih najnaprednejše AI — pri čemer ugotavlja, da nekateri sistemi zdaj lahko zaznajo, kdaj so ocenjevani, in temu ustrezno prilagodijo svoje vedenje.",
