  "Convert rights declarations into a workable licensing market instead of a binary open/closed web.": "Pretvoriti deklaracije pravic v delujoč trg licenciranja namesto binarnega odprtega/zaprtega spleta.",
  "Copied ✓": "Kopirano ✓",
  "Copy": "Kopiraj",
  "Correct positioning: independent research drafts, protocol proposals, and an open specification experiment.": "Pravilno pozicioniranje: neodvisni raziskovalni osnutki, predlogi protokolov in eksperiment odprte specifikacije.",
  "Corrected an earlier default: Belgium (BE) now maps to Dutch instead of French — Flemish speakers are the country’s majority (~60%) over Walloon French speakers (~40%).": "Popravljena prejšnja privzeta nastavitev: Belgija (BE) se zdaj preslika na nizozemščino namesto na francoščino — flamsko govoreči prebivalci predstavljajo večino prebivalstva države (~60%) v primerjavi z valonskimi frankofonskimi govorci (~40%).",
  "Corrected an earlier default: Kazakhstan (KZ) now maps to Kazakh instead of Russian, now that a Kazakh translation exists — the same kind of fix as the earlier Belgium correction.": "Popravljena prejšnja privzeta nastavitev: Kazahstan (KZ) se zdaj preslika na kazaščino namesto na ruščino, saj zdaj obstaja kazaški prevod — enaka vrsta popravka kot prejšnji popravek za Belgijo.",
  "Could AI Be Conscious?": "Could AI Be Conscious?",
  "Crawler access rules": "Pravila dostopa za pajke",
  "Crawler simulator": "Simulator pajkov",
  "Currency": "Valuta",
  "Custom tier": "Prilagojena raven",
  "Daily Nous reports on a retracted Journal of Medical Ethics submission containing multiple fabricated, AI-hallucinated references — complete with fake university affiliations and defunct email addresses — that the author reportedly left uncorrected even after being given a chance to fix proofs. The piece contrasts this with Bioethics, whose automated reference-checking would have caught the problem, and argues the real bottleneck isn't detection technology (one commenter's script flagged the fake citations in under a minute) but unpaid reviewer labor and publishing incentives that reward throughput over scrutiny.": "Daily Nous poroča o umaknjenem prispevku, poslanem reviji Journal of Medical Ethics, ki je vseboval številne izmišljene, s strani umetne inteligence halucinirane reference — vključno z lažnimi univerzitetnimi pripadnostmi in neobstoječimi e-poštnimi naslovi — ki jih avtor domnevno ni popravil niti potem, ko je dobil priložnost za popravek krtačnih odtisov. Prispevek to primerja z revijo Bioethics, katere avtomatizirano preverjanje referenc bi težavo odkrilo, in trdi, da resnična ovira ni tehnologija za odkrivanje (skripta enega od komentatorjev je lažne navedbe označila v manj kot minuti), temveč neplačano delo recenzentov in založniške spodbude, ki nagrajujejo obseg dela namesto temeljite presoje.",
  "Data free-riding vs. trillion-dollar AI valuations": "Zastonjkarstvo pri podatkih proti vrednotenjem umetne inteligence v vrednosti bilijonov dolarjev",
  "DeepMind CEO calls for an independent standards body to regulate frontier AI": "DeepMind CEO calls for an independent standards body to regulate frontier AI",
  "Demis Hassabis proposed a FINRA-style regulator for frontier model releases: labs would submit models for review up to 30 days before deployment, voluntary at first, with a path toward mandatory compliance in the US market.": "Demis Hassabis je predlagal regulatorja po zgledu FINRA za objave najsodobnejših modelov: laboratoriji bi modele predložili v pregled do 30 dni pred uvedbo, sprva prostovoljno, s poznejšim prehodom v obvezno skladnost na trgu ZDA.",
  "Denied": "Zavrnjeno",
  "Deployable policy starter template": "Začetna predloga politike, pripravljena za uvedbo",
  "Deployable policy starter template at /downloads/agiright-policy-starter.zip — a minimal static site with the full machine-readable layer, ready for Cloudflare Pages or any static host.": "Začetna predloga politike, pripravljena za uvedbo, na /downloads/agiright-policy-starter.zip — minimalistično statično spletno mesto s celotnim strojno berljivim slojem, pripravljeno za Cloudflare Pages ali kateri koli drug statični gostiteljski strežnik.",
  "Deploying machine-readable policies on your site": "Uvajanje strojno berljivih politik na vašem spletnem mestu",
  "Disclaimer": "Izjava o omejitvi odgovornosti",
  "Distinct from human UI, SEO, or plain APIs, the AI Ingestion & Capability Layer gives websites a machine-facing architecture: a Manifest Layer (entry points like /llms.txt and /ai/manifest.json), a Corpus Layer (machine-readable knowledge), a Capability Layer (agent-callable tools), and a Governance Layer (provenance, licensing, versioning). Static-first, upgradeable toward APIs and MCP. Note: in this paper AICL names the ingestion architecture; on this site's protocol pages AICL refers to the AI Content Licensing Layer.": "Za razliko od uporabniškega vmesnika za ljudi, SEO ali navadnih API-jev AI Ingestion & Capability Layer spletnim mestom zagotavlja arhitekturo, usmerjeno k strojem: sloj manifesta (vstopne točke, kot sta /llms.txt in /ai/manifest.json), sloj korpusa (strojno berljivo znanje), sloj zmožnosti (orodja, ki jih lahko pokliče agent) in sloj upravljanja (izvor, licenciranje, verzioniranje). Prvenstveno statično, nadgradljivo proti API-jem in MCP. Opomba: v tem dokumentu AICL označuje arhitekturo zajemanja vsebin; na straneh protokolov tega spletnega mesta se AICL nanaša na sloj licenciranja vsebin AI.",
  "Do Large Language Models Possess a Theory of Mind? A Comparative Evaluation Using the Strange Stories Paradigm": "Do Large Language Models Possess a Theory of Mind? A Comparative Evaluation Using the Strange Stories Paradigm",
  "Docs": "Dokumentacija",
  "Docs / Examples": "Dokumentacija / Primeri",
  "Document library": "Knjižnica dokumentov",
  "Does AI have rights — and which framings are even coherent?": "Ali ima umetna inteligenca pravice — in kateri okviri so sploh koherentni?",
  "Download": "Prenesi",
  "Draft status": "Status osnutka",
  "EU AI Act: What Actually Applies on 2 August 2026": "EU AI Act: What Actually Applies on 2 August 2026",
  "Educational demo: HMAC-SHA256 with a shared secret, showing request-bound, expiring, verifiable license tokens. Production tokens should be signed asymmetrically, with the publisher’s public key discoverable under /.well-known/.": "Izobraževalna predstavitev: HMAC-SHA256 s skupno skrivnostjo, ki prikazuje na zahtevo vezane, časovno omejene in preverljive licenčne žetone. Produkcijski žetoni naj bodo podpisani asimetrično, pri čemer je javni ključ izdajatelja mogoče najti pod /.well-known/.",
  "Eight more /topics entries, this time researched by an AI agent rather than curated by hand — same rule as before: every source fetched and confirmed live, summaries an original paraphrase, before anything gets added. 14 entries total.": "Še osem vnosov v razdelku /topics, tokrat jih je raziskal agent AI namesto ročnega kuriranja — enako pravilo kot prej: vsak vir je pridobljen in v živo potrjen, povzetki so izvirna parafraza, preden se karkoli doda. Skupno 14 vnosov.",
  "Email": "E-pošta",
  "Emotion Concepts and Their Function in a Large Language Model": "Emotion Concepts and Their Function in a Large Language Model",
  "Empirical Research": "Empirične raziskave",
  "English edition →": "Angleška izdaja →",
  "Ensure openness is machine-executable — so goodwill is not discarded as legal uncertainty.": "Zagotoviti, da je odprtost strojno izvedljiva — da dobra volja ne bo zavržena zaradi pravne negotovosti.",
  "Epistemology": "Epistemologija",
  "Epistemology of Generative AI: The Geometry of Knowing": "Epistemology of Generative AI: The Geometry of Knowing",
  "Ethics & Moral Status": "Etika in moralni status",
